attractions.title: L'Aérolaf
attractions.description: NEW : Located in the Viking area, in the heart of the Park, this new generation rotating bar- offers a unique and dizzying experience. Once the visitor has chosen and paid for his drink at the foot of the bar, he leaves for a 35 meters high journey with his head in the clouds.

attractions.title: L'Aventure Astérix
attractions.description: As a tribute to the two authors René Goscinny and Albert Uderzo, this exhibition traces the story of the Asterix comic strip and shows how the characters evolved through the generations. Long-time fans will be delighted by the reconstruction of the authors’ office where the project was conceived, the original comic strip pages and the life-size characters you meet as you wander through the exhibition.
attractions.summary: The Astérix Adventure: An immersive journey through the Astérix cartoon

attractions.title: Attention Menhir !
attractions.description: For the first time in its history, the Park is offering an animated film in 4D, in a brand new 300-seat theatre, Les Studios Idéfix. First wander through the Camp of Totorum, then sit yourself down in the dynamic seats and experience a unique story full of twists and surprises, inspired by the cartoon:  pop-out effects, water, wind, smells…The illusion is complete in every sense..
attractions.summary: The new 4D attraction at Parc Astérix

attractions.title: Mission perdue
attractions.description:
Embark an expedition to the stars in search of a crew lost on a strange planet. A close encounter of the third kind. For real. 3D Experience. 
(Not recommended for under 12s)
attractions.summary: An expedition into space for a close encounter of the third kind.

attractions.title: Pégase Express
attractions.description:
According to the legend, Pegasus the winged horse was transformed by Zeus into a constellation that shines brightly in the firmament.
Here in the park, Pegasus whisks lucky visitors on a mythical, and somewhat eventful, journey. 
 
Pégase Express is a high-speed train journey on a crazy and eventful 1-kilometre long circuit.
There’s no loop the loop, but plenty of fabulous twists and turns and sensational ups and downs.
attractions.summary: The new mythical attraction

attractions.title: Discobélix
attractions.description: As everyone knows, Obelix fell into a cauldron of magic potion when he was little... That’s where he got his legendary strength. So when he decides to toss a giant discus, it turns and turns, unstoppable, creating a cycle of perpetual motion that’s almost godly. Climb aboard for a trip that can only be described as... superhuman!
attractions.summary: What happens when Obelix has a go at the discus throw? A whirlwind adventure, that’s what!

attractions.title: Petit Chêne Play Area
attractions.description: In this play area, children can explore little Gallic cabins to learn more about the forest. With slides, crazy wild boars to ride and all manner of games, this Petit Chêne is full of surprises!
attractions.summary: Nature lovers, mount your trusty boar to discover the wildlife of the area!

attractions.title: Panoramix Play Area
attractions.description: Panoramix has developed a great new way to travel through the forest. On this astonishing pathway through the trees young Gauls will encounter all sorts of animals. Get climbing!
attractions.summary: Come, young Gauls: venture into La Forêt d’Idéfix and meet all the druid’s friends!

attractions.title: Les Chaudrons
attractions.description: To start with, you’ll feel tiny. If Obelix fell into one of these pots, they must really be enormous (no offense to our standing stone deliveryman intended). Next, you’ll start to feel the strange effects of the potion: lightheadedness, euphoria and giggling fits... Now that’s magic!
attractions.summary: Will you experience the same side effects as Obelix when you fall into a cauldron of magic potion?

attractions.title: SOS Numérobis
attractions.description: The train leaving from SOS Numérobis will be departing from platform six. With its tight turns, ups and downs, this medium-sized roller coaster is all about speed and will delight little kids and big kids alike! These Egyptians sure are crazy...
attractions.summary: Are you sitting comfortably? Numérobis is driving this train, and we’re about to set off!

attractions.title: Hydrolix
attractions.description: Climb aboard your little boat and sail up the river to its source! Thanks to Hydrolix’s invention, it’s finally possible. Of course, it wouldn’t be any fun without a few surprises... Splish splash!
attractions.summary: With this incredible invention, you can keep your head above the water whilst you sail upstream...

attractions.title: L'Hydre de Lerne
attractions.description: Imagine the bravery it must have taken to face L'Hydre de Lerne, a dangerous monster with seven heads. Now it’s your turn! Once it’s got you in its tentacled clutches, L'Hydre will lift you up and whirl you around to daze you... The life of a demigod is no cakewalk!
attractions.summary: It takes brains as well as brawn to confront a seven-headed monster. Charge!

attractions.title: Aérodynamix
attractions.description: In this funny contraption, your willpower alone will keep you airborne. Pedal as hard as you can and you’ve made it: you’re flying!
attractions.summary: This druid is a genius: he created an attraction that will give you wings. Prepare for take-off!

attractions.title: Les Petits Drakkars
attractions.description: Budding Vikings, this is the attraction for you! Board! Starboard! Brave the turbulent waters and hold your course. Back on dry land, you’ll have tons of stories to tell about your adventures. Just think how they’ll envy you... A real pirate!
attractions.summary: The rebellious sea is rising... Brave the storm aboard these famous dragon-headed Viking ships.

attractions.title: Etamine
attractions.description: Etamine’s busy concocting her potions, and she needs your help mixing them. Stir, stir, stir - not long to go now! And in return for your time, Etamine will have you howling with laughter!
attractions.summary: What’s the secret behind a good potion? Mix it well, and stir, stir, stir...

attractions.title: Nationale 7
attractions.description: On Nationale 7 it’s the kids’ turn to take the wheel in these brightly coloured rattle traps. Let’s hit the road! On this highway to the holidays, you’ll discover a series of funny, unpredictable scenes. Take your time and enjoy the ride! Luckily, out here there’s no need to choose between driving and having fun... Just watch out for the speed cameras!
attractions.summary: Whether you’re on a paved trail or a tarmacked road, steer clear of traffic jams...

attractions.title: Les Petits Chars tamponneurs
attractions.description: You’ve always dreamed of this, and now you can really do it! Hold off the Roman invader behind the wheel of one of these Gallic bumper cars. This power struggle is a great opportunity to let off steam and have fun, without getting hurt!
attractions.summary: These cars run on magic potion... Repelling the Romans will be a piece of cake with these!

attractions.title: Epidemaïs Croisière
attractions.description: Off we go! This pleasant cruise around the indomitable village will introduce you to the main characters from Asterix’s adventures... As well as a Roman garrison in total uproar! Is it the one from Compendium or Totorum? No time to wonder: fighting comes first!
attractions.summary: Let’s push the boat out! It sure is nice to take a little break between battles.

attractions.title: L'Escadrille des As
attractions.description: Fire your engines, check the oil levels and open the throttle. Away we go! Aboard these little old-world planes, young pilots rise into the air in a patrol formation worthy of the greatest aviators of all time. The sky is yours!
attractions.summary: The sky isn’t going to fall on your head! Why not go to meet it yourself?

attractions.title: Le Carrousel de César
attractions.description: Select your steed: a horse, Obelix’s trousers, or a legionary’s back. Whichever you choose, hold on tight because we’re about to go! How many times will the carrousel spin round? Only Caesar knows!
attractions.summary: Come, see, and above all, have a blast: Emperor Julius Caesar is in charge!

attractions.title: Le Petit Train
attractions.description: It’s common knowledge that the druids know all the secrets of the forest and find the precious ingredients for their potions there. This little train takes our youngest visitors on a mini-tour to meet the Druids. Perhaps they’ll learn the recipe for magic potion...?
attractions.summary: The druids draw their magic powers from the forest. This journey is full of enchanted promise...

attractions.title: Le Grand Splatch
attractions.description: “You can’t play water games without getting your helmet wet,” as the old saying goes, and Le Grand Splatch is the perfect example! Drift along a river surrounded by greenery and filled with aquatic effects to discover the Gallic spirit for yourself. And the grand finale? Oh, just a little 11-metre drop!
attractions.summary: This boat trip isn’t as calm as it looks... Be prepared to get wet!

attractions.title: La Galère
attractions.description: Aboard this swinging ship, the waves are your worst enemy. Hopefully you won’t end up shipwrecked... but the boat is reeling dangerously! Back and forth, back and forth... Just don’t abandon ship!
attractions.summary: As an enormous tempest rages all around, only your courage will stop the boat from rocking!

attractions.title: Romus et Rapidus
attractions.description: Feel like taking a trip? Next stop: Rome! Just make sure you’re ready for a bit of rocking and rolling on your raft. The Gauls have sabotaged this scenic journey, which will soon turn into a shower for the brave souls who dared to come along. Laughs and splashes guaranteed!
attractions.summary: Apparently, when in Rome, the best way to travel is by river... But it’s not plain sailing!

attractions.title: Menhir Express
attractions.description: Ready to take over the helm from Obelix? Are you sure? Because delivering standing stones is far from relaxing. Board your floating menhir and follow its course to reach your destination. But watch out! Whirlwinds, eddies, pitching, lurching and jets of water are all part of the journey. Just what you needed to clear your mind... before the final 13-metre drop! Smile, you’re on camera... and soaked to the skin!
attractions.summary: Your mission: to steer a floating menhir to safety... whilst staying dry. Impossible?

attractions.title: Tonnerre de Zeus
attractions.description: Set off on a stunning circuit 30 metres high and reaching over 80kmph! Thunder along at the speed of lightning through ups, downs, spirals, humps and break-neck turns, all under the mocking gaze of Zeus himself.
attractions.summary: Here’s a challenge from Zeus: can you handle a dizzying descent from Olympia?

attractions.title: Vikings Play Area
attractions.description: You’d better have your sea legs if you want to be a real Viking! And that’s not all... On land as well as on the waves, Vikings are valiant warriors with bags of courage. A lesser known fact is that they love having fun on board a Viking drekar or in a big Viking house!
attractions.summary: Welcome, young Vikings: this is the play area for you!

attractions.title: L'Oxygénarium
attractions.description: Climb up to the very tops of the trees and take a deep breath of fresh air. Now that your brain is nice and oxygenated, you’re ready to fully appreciate the 195-metre descent in a gigantic circular raft. Breath-taking!
attractions.summary: At the top of this incredible invention, there’s no chance you’ll be short of air!

attractions.title: Lavomatix
attractions.description: Lavomatix has plenty of good intentions, but does he have the good inventions to go with them? Participate in a frantic race, driving a wooden laundry basket. There’s not much purpose to it, except to make you laugh! Hey! Did someone say “weird”?
attractions.summary: This crazy inventor’s attraction is squeaky clean and full of fun...

attractions.title: Le Vol d'Icare
attractions.description:
O great Sun! Aboard this weird winged contraption, let yourself be lifted skyward, closer and closer to our magnificent star. Then, to avoid getting burnt, begin your descent, which promises to be an exhilarating adventure for riders big and small.

This attraction is closed until 2017 season.
attractions.summary: Head for the sun! Up, up and up... The descent will bring you out in a cold sweat!

attractions.title: Enigmatix
attractions.description: Take a comfy seat in this carrier designed by Enigmatix the druid. A series of gentle rises and falls will then begin... Watch out for the side effects: laughter, screams and butterflies in your tummy!
attractions.summary: Roll up for a unique experience which will take you high... and low. Laughter guaranteed!

attractions.title: La Petite Tempête
attractions.description: The little sailors rush to the helms of their boats to brave the tempest. Rising and falling, it’s hard to sail on such a choppy sea! Meanwhile, the boats are turning round at crazy speeds. Luckily, Obelix is there to keep an eye on things and make sure you keep your sea legs!
attractions.summary: All hands on deck! Stay on course and try your best to withstand this violent storm.

attractions.title: OzIris
attractions.description: On OzIris, our inverted coaster, you’ll find yourself zipping along at over 90kmph, 40 metres off the ground! With vertical loops, sidewinders and hairpin turns... you’ll be lost for words (not to mention hieroglyphics)!
attractions.summary: With your feet dangling below you and your head in the clouds, you’re not going to land any time soon!

attractions.title: La Rivière d'Elis
attractions.description: Do just what Asterix and Obelix did in their time, and set off for Ancient Greece to meet a host of mythological characters and Greek gods. Seated comfortably in your boat, explore the Mediterranean gardens along the Elis and be transported to a magical world.
attractions.summary: Take your seat in a little boat and enjoy a divine tour of the Gardens of Olympia.

attractions.title: Le Mini Carrousel
attractions.description: This mini-carrousel will delight our youngest visitors. A horse, a swan, a camel or a colourful carriage? There’s something special for every young Gaul! After a few turns, they’ll become real knights, princesses, soldiers and adventurers. It’s a dream come true!
attractions.summary: Knights and princesses will always find the perfect steed here. Charge!

attractions.title: Les Espions de César
attractions.description: This perilous mission is reserved for the most valiant soldiers of the Roman legion! At the controls of your pedal-driven chariot, fly over the village of indomitable Gauls and try to steal the secret recipe for Panoramix’s magic potion. It’s no easy feat, and if you get caught, the park will deny all knowledge of this mission to Caesar’s glory...
attractions.summary: Outwit the vigilant Gauls and steal their magic potion recipe... Godspeed!

attractions.title: Les Petites Chaises Volantes
attractions.description: Aboard Les Petites Chaises Volantes, our young Gauls will transform into professional acrobats. Are they ready for a taste of this pleasant feeling of weightlessness? They’ll soon find out as they fly through the air!
attractions.summary: Whether they’re big or small, Les Chaises Volantes will always leave your head spinning!

attractions.title: Les Chevaux du Roy
attractions.description: This magnificent carrousel with two levels of wooden horses transports visitors of all ages back in time. In the Middle Ages, the Gauls never missed a chance to have fun; now, their medieval shields and coats of arms have been revised and updated to make you smile.
attractions.summary: Hear ye, hear ye, noblefolk! Prepare for a weird and wonderful trip back in time!

attractions.title: Les Chaises Volantes
attractions.description: Your steed? A chair. Its special power? Flying. Get ready for a unique experience. As the ride begins to turn, you’ll feel your feet leave the ground, and as it picks up speed, you’ll climb higher and higher. By Toutatis, you’re flying!
attractions.summary: Lift off and use centrifugal forces to defy the laws of gravity.

attractions.title: La Trace du Hourra
attractions.description: Freewheel to your heart’s content in an authentic Gallic bobsleigh! Experience an incomparable feeling of lightness as you glide along at 60kmph on La Trace du Hourra, and enjoy a new thrill with every turn. Who’d have thought you’d find a slip-sliding ride like this in Gaul?
attractions.summary: Experience sliding like never before aboard this Gallic bobsleigh... Incredible!

attractions.title: Le Cheval de Troie
attractions.description: You need to arm yourself with courage to go down in history. Especially when it involves confronting Le Cheval de Troie! Up on this platform, 12 metres off the ground, you have one objective as you buck and reel to and fro: to hold on tight! Don’t worry, though: once you get used to the turbulence, you’re in for more laughs than screams!
attractions.summary: Twelve metres off the ground, place your blind faith in an unruly steed...

attractions.title: Goudurix
attractions.description: It all begins with a gentle climb, perfect for admiring the scenery... But that won’t last long! After plunging back to earth at over 75kmph and racing through seven loops, each one crazier than the last, you won’t know which way is up! They don’t call Goudurix one of the most head-spinning coasters in Europe for nothing... Viking’s honour!
attractions.summary: Are you a real risk-taker? Then you’ll love this roller coaster and every one of its seven loops!
